🪔 Diwali Sales Data Analysis: Unwrapping Festive Trends Through Data

Festivals are not just about celebration—they are also a goldmine of data.
In this project, I explored Diwali sales data to understand customer behavior, product performance, and the key factors driving revenue during one of the biggest shopping seasons.

Starting from raw data, I performed data cleaning, preprocessing, and exploratory data analysis to uncover meaningful insights. By analyzing different variables such as gender, age group, occupation, and product categories, I was able to identify patterns in purchasing behavior and spending habits.

Some key highlights from this project:
🔹 Identified which customer segments contribute the most to sales
🔹 Analyzed top-performing product categories during Diwali
🔹 Explored spending patterns across different demographics
🔹 Visualized trends to make insights more clear and actionable

This project helped me strengthen my skills in:
✔️ Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
✔️ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
✔️ Data Visualization using Python
✔️ Extracting business insights from data

What I found most interesting is how data can tell a complete story—behind every purchase, there is a pattern, and behind every trend, there is an opportunity for businesses to grow smarter.

Projects like this continue to motivate me as I move forward in my journey in Data Science and Engineering. I’m excited to keep learning, building, and turning data into impactful insights.
